<taxonomicName id="31BE627AB7F4B0374D99DB98E8741C16" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. lehmanniana" order="Poales" pageId="37" pageNumber="160" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="lehmanniana">
<emphasis id="96F48F1084ADFB851966A0F9D6302547" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="160">M. lehmanniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Henr. ranging from Costa Rica to Colombia (
<bibRefCitation id="60B2B08E139334E0F9D4D0802480EDCA" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1756-1051.1990.tb01786.x" author="Laegaard, S" journalOrPublisher="Nordic Journal of Botany" pageId="58" pageNumber="181" pagination="437 - 441" refId="B18" refString="Laegaard, S, Sanchez Vega, I, 1990. Three new species of Muhlenbergia and Uniola (Poaceae) from northern Peru. Nordic Journal of Botany 10 (4): 437 - 441, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1756-1051.1990.tb01786.x" title="Three new species of Muhlenbergia and Uniola (Poaceae) from northern Peru." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1756-1051.1990.tb01786.x" volume="10" year="1990">
<normalizedToken id="CEF8890A86B60885D8DBC19E14CBB934" originalValue="Lægaard">Laegaard</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken id="EE592CA027EC9E47F9741F39A10905DC" originalValue="Sánchez">Sanchez</normalizedToken>
Vega 1990
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="0CD0A9335B122856D469CFD2A6A1D080" author="Giraldo-Canas, D" journalOrPublisher="Caldasia" pageId="58" pageNumber="181" pagination="269 - 302" refId="B7" refString="Giraldo-Canas, D, Peterson, P, 2009. El genero Muhlenbergia (Poaceae: Chloridoideae: Cynodonteae: Muhlenbergiinae) en Colombia. Caldasia 31: 269 - 302" title="El genero Muhlenbergia (Poaceae: Chloridoideae: Cynodonteae: Muhlenbergiinae) en Colombia." volume="31" year="2009">
<normalizedToken id="58067309FD75F6A94D78BD8FF2C4D37D" originalValue="Giraldo-Cañas">Giraldo-Canas</normalizedToken>
and Peterson 2009
</bibRefCitation>
) are morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="31326C9A6749101AF16AA0B49B6B7060" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. maxima" order="Poales" pageId="37" pageNumber="160" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="maxima">
<emphasis id="FE0CF195E75ABDD9F5E19EB75567857A" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="160">M. maxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="DAF17F76104BDE1184BB0DBBFF33E9A5" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Muhlenbergia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Muhlenbergia maxima" order="Poales" pageId="37" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maxima">
<emphasis id="BAA36EA433207DB9754E422A02A1734F" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="160">Muhlenbergia maxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="DD3BF848CCB4D24379072487898FB631" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. inaequalis" order="Poales" pageId="37" pageNumber="160" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="inaequalis">
<emphasis id="EE220422D412FCA59AFF1ED52E708887" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="160">M. inaequalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="EDB40C0AB7547A28D1F65173E707C247" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. lehmanniana" order="Poales" pageId="37" pageNumber="160" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="lehmanniana">
<emphasis id="9CD630E298F278D3A0C6480501103D8A" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="160">M. lehmanniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having shorter lemmatal awns and a longer ligule than 
<taxonomicName id="DD6704789D3D9571B239001696E99F23" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. inaequalis" order="Poales" pageId="37" pageNumber="160" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="inaequalis">
<emphasis id="A61CFD285DC2AEB02041334B66E179A1" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="160">M. inaequalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(0.5-1.5 mm long) and a shorter ligule than 
<taxonomicName id="0C44D8286E306EE6504DA1CEF2D60328" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. lehmanniana" order="Poales" pageId="37" pageNumber="160" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="lehmanniana">
<emphasis id="C727734CC15454093FBBE0B54D1756C7" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="160">M. lehmanniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(1-2.5 cm long). There is not much genetic variation among all members of 
<taxonomicName id="366095796DFEE152476E8D9DA1BBE496" authority="subg. Trichochloa" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraspecific-rank="subg." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M." order="Poales" pageId="37" pageNumber="160" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus" subGenus="Trichochloa">M. subg. Trichochloa</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="C31DFF9C51804190174D1FA52208CE90" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2010.01.018" author="Peterson, PM" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="58" pageNumber="181" pagination="580 - 598" refId="B37" refString="Peterson, PM, Romaschenko, K, Johnson, G, 2010a. A classification of the Chloridoideae (Poaceae) based on multi-gene phylogenetic trees. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 55 (2): 580 - 598, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2010.01.018" title="A classification of the Chloridoideae (Poaceae) based on multi-gene phylogenetic trees." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2010.01.018" volume="55" year="2010 a">Peterson et al. (2010a)</bibRefCitation>
and a detailed population genetic study of these three South American species is needed to interpret their evolutionary history.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
